         I had a pet duel with a beastlord friend. I summoned a spec hits 57. (I didn't bother to resummon a 59 hitter, it's 10pp a try!!).  My friend is level 58 with his 2nd best pet. His pet is always the same level and con'ed blue to me at level 60.  After full buffs, we started the duel. His pet seemed to proc alot...</P><P>At the end my pet lost and his pet had about 1 pixel of hps... It was too close to say which pet is better. However, I learned a few things. Beastlord pet can be tough cause Beastlord has lots shaman buffers! They can buff their pets with STR, STA, DEX, AGI, Hp and regen. Also my friend still has a pet upgrade at level 60 and even better shaman buffers for his pet!    </P><P>So next time if you happen to have a pet duel with a beastlor, try do it with pet haste buffer only lol.  It's just like dueling a magi pet. If he uses damage shield on his pet, then our pet will always lose.</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
