         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>mage pets should own our pets, on a side note.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Where is this written that mage pets should be superior to necro pets? This is nonsense. Necros can summon pets at lvl one. Mages can't summon a pet until level 4! Mages should be masters of summoning not exclusively the  masters of pets. Please show me where it says that mages should have the most powerful pets. You can't because it doesn't exist.</P><P>This line about mages being masters of pets has been floating around for the last year on these boards and trust me it will be used by some as and excuse not to get our pets upgraded by the new breed of "root dotting" necros who rolled up their necros a few months ago.</P><P>Mages are given 4 unique pets with unique abilities. That is their power and their advantage. Necro's do not have pets that have the incredible variety and utility that mage pets have.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote> Yeah they should.</P><P>Pets and nukes are the ONLY thing mages get to fight mobs. Mages are pet classes, they rely on them several times more than any necro ever will.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>So necromancers aren't pet classes? C'mon! Mages get an amazing arsenal of direct damage spells not to mention one of the best DAMAGE SHIELDS out there. They get pet sow. They get to summon the Mask of Mardu to give a better haste to their pet. They can literally chain cast pets with super low mana costs for all of their pets. Sorry I don't buy this nonsense about mages being the master of pets at all.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote> Now I'm not saying a 51 mage cast should kill a 59 necro cast and have 50% health left over, but at the very least it should be a close fight.</P><P><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>It takes 2 twice as long to get from lvl 49 to lvl 59 as it does to get to from lvl 1 to lvl 49. Emissary of Thule should kick the ass of a lvl 49 mage pet into next Tuesday. No, it shouldn't be close either.</P><P>All pet classes need serious upgrades to their pets AC, HPS, resistances and yes damage. I spent 200pp in peridots in Plane of Growth tonite trying to summon blue pets. Blue spectre pet can hit for 53 damage and still be blue if you can believe it. Emissary of Thule being beaten by our level 49 pet is an outrage to the necromancer class. Then to have the 51 mage pet beat the 49 necro pet with 50% health to spare even more an indictment of the weakness of our pets.</P><P>Pets can't upgrade themselves. Pets can't wear resist gear. Pet's can't even take advantage of group buffs. Pets and pathing can agro a whole dungeon on you. Pets steal experience but don't use that experience to level or improve their skills. Pets won't give weapons back. Pets graphics are horribly broken since Luclin. It goes on and on.</P><P>Pets have been seriously neglected by Verant for the past 3 years since the orginal EQ. Now high level mages and necros escpecially at level 60 are almost non-existant and quitting in droves. No bloody wonder. The last postive change to necro pets was making EOT immune to fear last year. That's it. Well that's all fine and well but honestly that pet will be dead in 30 secs due to the AE's.</P><P>Verant it's time caster balancing was changed to pet class balancing. Wizards have been getting all of the love from Verant since before the release of Luclin. Guilds like FOH even talk about wizard "zerging". Enchanters can Dire Charm the fiercest mobs and have no restrictions on mob type and they are always in demand in groups. It's now time to show mages and necros the love.</P><P>Dornette<BR>60 necromancer (un-retired)<BR>The Nameless<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
